Part 1 of a pre-intermediate course in English. 
The course takes you from level A2 to B1, through communicative activities. In the autumn term we will cover the first six units in the study book. There will be a test after every second unit. 
The grammar part will cover present and past tenses and the use of articles.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to develop your listening, speaking, writing and reading skills at levels A2-B1, in a communicative context. .Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will have acquired the necessary vocabulary and grammar in a way that it covers all four language skills and are able to cope with everyday topics treated during the course. Students understand and are able to write texts on different subjects, are able to have conversations and understand speech.
